div.p:
COme and harken unto
me, ô all yee that
feare the Lord, and I will
shew you what thing hee
hath done for my Soule,
he hath created me, hee
hath brought me into
life, and hath so disposed
of mee that I am,
A living soule,
and not
a sensles thing;
A Man, not a Beast;
Civill, not barbarous;
Freeborne, not a slave;
Legittimate, not a bastard;
Of honest parentage, not
of base or Ignominious;
Of understanding, not
blockish;


Sound in sences, not blind
or deafe;
Sound in Limbs, not
lame or maimed;
Well brought up, not
forlorne or exposed.
A Christian, not a Pagan;
Peaceable not quarelsome;
Cleare of dangers, not
swallowed up by them;
Cleere of infamy, not
wounded in credit;
Of sufficient estate, not
forced to flatter; or
borrow.
